text:
Battery Park: A southward view across from No. 17 State Street, showing the sea wall and a new ticket booth. In the background appears Bedloe's Island with the Statue of Liberty there and beyond the New Jersey shoreline. Passing down the Bay is the French liner "S.S. Normandie". This set consists of 2 views.
September 16, 1936.
P.L. Sperr.
title: Manhattan: Battery Park Sea Wall and new ticket booth.

text:
(1)
Battery Park: The northwestern corner of same, viewed in a westward direction from No. 17 State Street and showing across the North (Hudson) River the New Jersey shoreline.  The structure shown on the right is the Whitehall Building.
September 16, 1936.
P.L. Sperr.

(2)
A similar view and showing also the S.S. "Normandie" and the new Downtown Athletic Club.
September 16, 1936.
P.L. Sperr.

(3)
A portion of the view seen in No. 2 and emphasising the aforementioned structure.
September 16, 1936.
P.L. Sperr.
